<br>
There were brief periods in Evequest history that did not have rampant bugs.  All other times something(s) is broken at one time or another.  It is the nature of the game.  It is ever changing.  Verant is always attempting to improve EQ.  EQ will never stand still.  At least in the foreseeable future.<br>
<br>
I presume you are talking about the long zoning times or some computer configurations that do not work so well with the latest expansion.  Truth is, only a very miniscule fraction of players cannot play the game.  Verant has been working hard to fix the most aggregious bugs, and are slowly working to fix the other hardware compatibility problems.  Check <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.everquest.com">www.everquest.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> to make sure your computer hardware can handle Everquest.  Then go out and buy another copy.  IF...you do not want a social life anymore.<br>
